thoughts.reasoning_problem:
Context: Pets are allowed in some managed buildings. [BG] A deposit is required to rent an apartment in a managed building. The security deposit can be either equal to one month's rent or more. Fluffy is Tom's cat. Cats are pets. The Olive Garden is a managed building. The monthly rent at the Olive Garden is $2000. Tom will rent an apartment in a managed building if and only if he is allowed to move in with Fluffy, and the security deposit is no more than $1500. 2000$ is more than $1500.
Question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? The security deposit at the Olive Garden is either $2000 or more.
Options: A) True B) False C) Uncertain
raw_logic_programs:
Predicates:
Pets(x) ::: x is a pet.
ManagedBuilding(x) ::: x is a managed building.
AllowedIn(x, y) ::: x is allowed in y.
Deposit(x, y) ::: x is a deposit required to rent y.
EqualOrMore(x, y) ::: x is equal to or more than y.
Cat(x) ::: x is a cat.
Owner(x, y) ::: x is the owner of y.
Rent(x, y) ::: x rents y.
MoveInWith(x, y, z) ::: x moves in with y to z.
MonthlyRent(x, y) ::: x is the monthly rent of y.
Premises:
∃x (ManagedBuilding(x) ∧ Pets(x)) ::: Pets are allowed in some managed buildings.
∀x (ManagedBuilding(x) → Deposit(x, apartment)) ::: A deposit is required to rent an apartment in a managed building.
∀x (Deposit(x, apartment) → EqualOrMore(x, oneMonthRent)) ::: The security deposit can be either equal to one month's rent or more.
Cat(fluffy) ∧ Owner(tom, fluffy) ::: Fluffy is Tom's cat.
∀x (Cat(x) → Pets(x)) ::: Cats are pets.
ManagedBuilding(oliveGarden) ::: The Olive Garden is a managed building.
MonthlyRent(2000, oliveGarden) ::: The monthly rent at the Olive Garden is $2000.
Rent(tom, apartment) ↔ (MoveInWith(tom, fluffy, apartment) ∧ ¬EqualOrMore(deposit, 1500)) ::: Tom will rent an apartment in a managed building if and only if he is allowed to move in with Fluffy, and the security deposit is no more than $1500.
2000 > 1500 ::: 2000$ is more than $1500.
Conclusion:
EqualOrMore(deposit, 2000) ::: The security deposit at the Olive Garden is either $2000 or more.

∀x (ManagedBuilding(x) → Deposit(x, apartment)) ::: A deposit is required to rent an apartment in a managed building.
∀x (Deposit(x, apartment) → EqualOrMore(x, oneMonthRent)) ::: The security deposit can be either equal to one month's rent or more.
Cat(fluffy) ∧ Owner(tom, fluffy) ::: Fluffy is Tom's cat.
∀x (Cat(x) → Pets(x)) ::: Cats are pets.
ManagedBuilding(oliveGarden) ::: The Olive Garden is a managed building.
MonthlyRent(2000, oliveGarden) ::: The monthly rent at the Olive Garden is $2000.
Rent(tom, apartment) ↔ (MoveInWith(tom, fluffy, apartment) ∧ ¬EqualOrMore(deposit, 1500)) ::: Tom will rent an apartment in a managed building if and only if he is allowed to move in with Fluffy, and the security deposit is no more than $1500.
2000 > 1500 ::: 2000$ is more than $1500.
Conclusion:
EqualOrMore(deposit, 2000) ::: The security deposit at the Olive Garden is either $2000 or more.
